<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10113] Undroppable messages can be dropped if message queue gets large</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10113</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When outgoing messages are queued, OutboundTcpConnection checks the size of backlog, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-2.1/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/net/OutboundTcpConnection.java#L150&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;if it gets more than 1024, it drops expired messages silently from the backlog&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;expireMessages()&lt;/tt&gt; just checks message&apos;s timeout, which can be &lt;tt&gt;request_timeout_in_ms&lt;/tt&gt; (10 sec default) for non- read/write message, and does not check if its droppable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
